### QUESTION
Think of everyday situations that simulation could analyze.
What aspects of the situation make the simulation approach specifically appropriate for analyzing the situation
(i.e., think about and explain why simulation would be specifically better than experimenting in the real world).
What aspects of sustainability can you incorporate into the simulation


### ANSWER
There are two aspects of the situation that make the stimulation specifically more appropriate for analyzing the situation, which are variability and prediction.
Stimulation can be used in different situations in real life. An example is weather stimulation.
By using stimulation in weather prediction, we can predict the path of a tornado.
Therefore, we can prepare countermeasures for it, for example, evacuating citizens from areas where the tornado would come.